        news.setNews("\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e It Ends With Us: A Novel-Colleen Hoover\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe latest novel from New York Times best-selling author, Colleen Hoover is crafted with love. Sometimes it is the one who loves you who hurts you the most. Life wasn't easy for Lily always, But it never stopped her from working hard for the life she loved. A journey from a small town in Maine where she grew up, she graduated from college, moved to Boston, and started her own business. When she meets a gorgeous neurosurgeon named Ryle Kincaid, everything in Lily’s life suddenly seems too good to be true. Lily falls head over heel's for him, but his attitude to relationships are disturbing. Even as Lily finds herself becoming the exception to his “no dating” rule, she can’t help but wonder what made him that way in the first place. Atlas Corrigan, her first love and a link to the past she left behind comes back to her often. When Atlas suddenly reappears, everything Lily has built with Ryle is threatened. What will happen now? Collen Hoover is all set with a heart-wrenching tale of love, played by people too full of human emotions.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003ePaperback Amazon price: Rs 349\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eKindle edition: Rs 284.05\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e Ms Draupadi Kuru: After the Pandavas -Trisha Das\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eDraupadi is bored of her picture perfect life in heaven. It's the same routine for the past few thousand of years. Her only way to escape is lord Krishna, who never says no to her. So she gets her gang of women together-Amba, Kunti, Gandhari and off they go to New Delhi, on Earth, where things have changed and some things still the same. Kunti gets attached to a street urchin, Draupadi lands up in a television studio and Amba finds the one thing that can never be hers back in heaven . Gandhari has something special to say about all of it. Will thirty days they have for all their partying satisfy them?\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003ePaperback Amazon price: Rs 234\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eKindle edition: Rs 222.30\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e Closed Casket-Sophie Hannah\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eLady Athelinda Playford has planned a house party at her mansion in Clonakilty, County Cork, but it is not a usual gathering. Lady Playford summons her lawyer to make an urgent change to her will and intends to announce it at the dinner that night. She has decided to leave all that she has to someone who has only weeks to live. She decides to leave her children penniless. Among Lady Playford’s guests are two men she has never met-the famous Belgian detective, Hercule Poirot and Inspector Edward Catchpool of Scotland Yard. Poirot starts to wonder if Lady Playford expects a murderer to strike. Yes, the crime is committed in spite of Poirot’s best efforts to stop it. The victim is not who he expected it to be. Wil Poirot be successful in identifying the culprit? Will he unravel the mystery?\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003ePaperback Amazon price: Rs 279\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eHardcover Amazon price: Rs 1399.63\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eKindle edition: Rs 246.05\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e A Midsummer's Equation-Keigo Higashino\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eWhen a man's body is discovered at the base of some cliffs in the small resort town of Hari Cove, the police at first suspect a tragic accident, a misstep that cost the man his life. But the mystery only starts when it is found out that the cause of death was actually carbon monoxide poisoning. The investigation begins and Manabu Yukawa, the physicist known as 'Detective Galileo', is in Hari Cove to speak at a conference on a planned underwater mining operation. Yukawa uncovers the hidden relationship behind the tragic events that led to this murder after a series of twist and surprising events.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003ePaperback Amazon price: Rs 211\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eHardcover Amazon price: Rs 1352\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eKindle edition: Rs 200.45\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e How the Secret Changed My Life: Real People. Real Stories-Rhonda Byrne\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eHow the Secret Changed My Life presents a selection of the most heart-warming and moving stories in one inspirational volume. Every story provides an authentic, real-life illustration of the pathway that leads to success in every area of life: money, health, relationships, love, family and career. The book from time to time shows again that no one is excluded from living the life of their dreams.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eHardcover Amazon price: Rs 489\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them: The Original Screenplay-J K Rowling\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eWhen Magizoologist Newt Scamander arrives in New York, he thinks it to be just a brief stopover. But his magical case is misplaced and some of Newt's fantastic beasts escape, spelling trouble for everyone. Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them marks the screenwriting debut of J.K. Rowling, author of the beloved and internationally best-selling Harry Potter books. Featuring a cast of remarkable characters, this is epic, adventure-packed storytelling at its best.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003eHardcover Amazon price: Rs 489\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e");
